message: I'm new to WP and have been told to edit modestly at first.  This is my first attempt and I'm a little nervous and timid so I hope this small edit is OK to the God-like admins of WP.  Please Gods of WP keep some of this on the page.  You're much cleverer than me so I leave it with you to edit further.

Sadly some admin nerd is going to have to protect the page because history needs to record that this was all predictable over a decade ago and these time entries form a history for the next civilization - that the catastrophe was very obvious to some but this knowledge was suppressed by others.

I'm extremely thankful for the acknowledgement of "good faith" edits.  They are indeed in good faith.  The bad faith comes from the whole financial system, but these edits are "good faith" edits.  As God himself would acknowledge.
Minor edit to take into account unpredicted (and impossible to predict) current events
This was written in 2006/07.  Think about that.  Predictable nearly two decades ago.  How stupid are the mainstream economists who cannot predict 2 weeks ahead.  Or how evil.

This new wording gives the impression that "banks don't have enough money" or something -- a bad misimpression for our readers. It should be easy to adjust this language. Also, be aware that the lead must reflect sourced content in the article text. New ideas or explanations cannot first be introduced into the lead.
Reverted good faith [[WP:GF]] edits to the lead.  The previous version was more understandable to the layperson, rather than someone knowledgeable in finance.
This disaster of a document should not be used as a reference for anything.
You have been indefinitely blocked from editing because it appears that you are not here to [[WP:NOTHERE|build an encyclopedia]].
